RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Ya rds).

CLAIM.OWNER: BW and HTS Stables LLC and Grudzien Jason G

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HIGH DONNA raced from off of the pace in the four path, improved position while racing in hands down the back side, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, circled the rest of the field, responded well to encouragement and took command at the eighth pole, drew off for the win. PINCHING PENNIES stalked the pace setter from the three path, launched a bid at the three eights pole, took the lead by the quarter pole, battled with another rival on the outside, could not h old that one off but was bale to secure second place honors. LACEY'S STAR was off in the middle of the field, raced in the three path, bid at the three eighths pole, split horses in the turn, raced in the two path down the stretch and split rivals again at the eighth pole closing well enough to get up for third. MISS ARKANSAS raced from off of the pace, trailed the field while racing in the four path, made one run, starting picking up the pace and gaining ground at the half mile pole, circled the field in the five path, shifted into the six path in the upper stretch, closed well. MARK WITH AN E was off a tough slow, raced from off of the pace in the three path, made one run, split horses through the turn, stayed to the inside and raced in the two path for the stretch drive, responded to encouragement and out finished the rest. POQUITO LADY stalked the pace from the five path but never got involved. REAUX BINA vied for the lead, raced on the rail while setting the early fractions, was collared at the quarter pole and gave way. ABBEY CAKES was off mid pack, raced to the inside, saved ground through out, was in contention in the stretch and had no late kick. LA VALEDORA raced in the middle of the field, raced on the rail, then steadily faded after the three eighths pole.

GOTTEMINABIND was off in the middle of the field, raced in the four path, improved position, circled the field in the six path, raced widest of all in the stretch, closed willingly getting up for second. MOR KISSES stalked the early leader for the two path, willingly drew beside the leader after the half mile pole, tried to match strides but could not sustain the bid, switched leads late finishing flat. JULIO CHOICE stalked the leader from the four path, raced in between horses, smartly angled to the inside entering the upper stretch but had no late rally. T J'S FIRST raced from off of the pace, made one run, raced in the three and four paths, closed well finding her best stride late. CECE WAVE stalked the pace, raced on the rail, struggled to switch leads and raced an even race. OCEAN FLEET raced from mid pack in the six path, circled horses in the turn, raced six wide in the stretch but to no avail. REINA ACES raced from mid pack in the four path, maintained that position through out. BLESS D'SOUTH raced from the middle of the field on the rail but was never involved. COUSIN VICKIE trailed through out.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 3 7 1/2F Turf CR: 82. Claiming Purse 14000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main tra ck at one mile and seventy yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BASKET CASE stalked from the inside, was patiently waiting for the cue, stayed right off the leader until the eighth pole, was cued and responded well by jumping up and passing the front runner, drawing away willingly for the win. WATCH THIS MUNNY was off a bit slow, raced from off of the pace, stayed on the rail and saved ground, made one run and gained ground willingly through the turn on the inside, continued to build momentum and gain ground into the stretch, was closing fast and angled out into the six path to pass rivals in the furlong ground, was almost to the leader and ran out of room, once he recovered from the break WATCH THIS MUNNY ran a great second. GIRL ON THE GO raced from the middle of the field, raced on the fence and saved ground the whole trip, improved through the turn, closed in the stretch getting up for third. THE RAGE OF ART stalked from the four path, circled the field in the five path as improved position, was in contention then tired late. KHOZY TAP stalked the pace setter from the four path then faded. MALLY'S MONSOON vied for the lead, raced on the rail, set the pace, led until the eighth pole then was collared by the eventual winner and retreated. CAPETOWN CANDY was off in the middle of the field ,raced in the four and five path and raced an even race. SANTANGELO raced off of the pace in the three path and was never involved. TIZ MY PLAN stalked from the four path, raced in between horses, shifted into the five path in the upper stretch and faded. LAYLA'S SONG was off a step slow, raced in the four and five path, but made no impact. SHEZA CAT showed little.

(If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at 1 Mile and 70 Yards).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WORLD WAR stalked the leader from the four path, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, took the lead by the quarter pole, was cued at the eighth pole and she responded well by kicking into another gear and finishing strong for the win. DADDYMADEMEDOIT raced from mid pack in the three path, was in between rivals as she improved and advanced into the second tier of contestants, launched a bid at the three eighths pole, split rivals as she gained position, was in a nice spot down the stretch but did not have enough today. GASTOWN hopped at the start, was off slow, was given time to find her legs, made one run in the five and six paths, hit her best stride in the stretch, closed willingly getting up for third. WATRUGONNADOKAREN raced from the middle of the field in the four path, launched a bid at the half mile pole, shifted into the five path and circled the field through the turn, was closing in the stretch, had drawn beside the set running second, passed them, threatening the eventual winner but the gave way in the last sixteenth. QUINN ELLA was off in the middle of the field, raced in the five path, moved at the half, then finished even. DISCREET SMILE stalked the pace from the three path, advanced, challenged for the lead at the five sixteenth, briefly led in between calls, then tired. SWEET PERFECTION made no impact. TEXAS BLUEBONNET showed little. B'S LIL' BUMBLEBEE flashed early speed.
